data.content:
Đại từ
(cách viết khác anyone)
bất cứ ai
did anybody see you?
Có [bất cứ] ai thấy anh không?
he left without speaking to anybody else
anh ta bỏ đi mà không nói [bất cứ] ai cả
người nào, ai
is anybody there?
Có ai ở đó không?
(trong câu phủ định) nhân vật quan trọng
she wasn't anybody before she got that job
trước khi có được công việc đó, bà ta chẳng là gì cả

pronoun
any person :anyone
Did anybody call?
I don't know how anybody can believe that.
I thought I heard someone outside, but when I looked there wasn't anybody there. [=no one was there]
An accident like that could happen to anybody.
You have to be a member to go there. They won't let just anybody in.
Everybody who's anybody [=every important or well-known person] was there.
She arrived 10 minutes before anybody else. [=before any other person]
used when asking a question that could be answered by any of the people in a group
Does anybody know where my keys are? [=do any of you know where my keys are?]
Would anybody like more coffee?
